translated: Isberg, Sven Paul Axel, certified doctor. Karlsborg, born on 17/10/09 in Stockholm to Captain v. Flottan Paul I. and Astrid Ernberg. Married in 1939 to Karin Granqvist. He passed his high school exams in 1928, received a Bachelor of Science in Medicine in 1932 and a Medical Doctorate in 1938, all in Stockholm. He was appointed as a railway doctor in Storlien from 1934-37 and 1938, assistant doctor at Hörby Hospital, and second assistant doctor at Broby Sanatorium for a short time in 1938. He worked as an assistant doctor at Betaniasyst-rarnas Sick Home in 1939. He was appointed as the Navy Chief Medical Officer in 1939 and is currently the Vice Chief Medical Officer at the Garn Military Hospital in Karlsborg.
